{
  "metadata": {
    "title": "Stuffed Courgettes with Pine Nut Salsa",
    "description": "Stuffed vegetables would definitely be part of my last meal – I love them! Traditionally, stuffing vegetables has always been a bit of a labour of love but, here, a lot of labour has been removed without cost to the love. Try to get large courgettes, if you can: you’ll be able to scrape them more easily without damaging them and have plenty of flesh to stuff back inside. A mix of yellow and green courgettes also looks great, if you can get hold of both. You can make the stuffing a day ahead so that the courgettes are ready to be stuffed and grilled.",
    "servings": 4,
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "totalTime": "25min",
